    <note type="dates"><date>1663–1718</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>French-born journalist and translator. Of a Huguenot family. Emigrated to London in 1685, becoming an English citizen in 1686. Published a revision of Thomas Urquhart’s translation of the first three books of Rabelais’s <hi rend="italic">Gargantua and Pantagruel</hi>, and translated the fourth and fifth books.</p></note>
